HEADWORD: Saloop
<hw>Sa*loop"</hw> <pr>(s⟦adot⟧*l⟦oomac⟧p")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An
aromatic drink prepared from sassafras bark and other ingredients, at
one time much used in London.</def> <rj><au>J. Smith (Dict. Econ.
Plants).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Saloop bush</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>an
Australian shrub (<spn>Rhagodia hastata</spn>) of the Goosefoot family,
used for fodder.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

